Most people who are settled into a habit of spending more than they
earn will run into a 'reality wall' when they try to reduce their debt
load. They believe that they have eliminated every luxury and left
only the necessities, but are still spending too much.  Success
requires a real change in what you believe you need.

If your lifestyle was that much higher than your income, it means that
your idea of necessities is very screwed-up. It's going to hurt more
than you thought to come back to reality.
