all your expenses to the bone and it still doesn't make a difference,
maybe you need to earn more?

In my own struggle with credit card debt (paid off $16,000 while
unemployed), I found that it is frequently easier to just find a way
to make more money rather than torture yourself with yet another
budget cut.  I didn't give up Starbucks while paying off my debt.  In
fact, I gave up very little in the way of luxuries at all; most of the
