Pay cash for everything. No cash, no purchase.  If in a given month you
throw your cash around frivolously and then miss some required payments
(utilities, car, house, ins, etc), the bite in the ass you'll get from those
entities will cause you to pay them first the next time.  If you run out of
cash before you run out of month, you may have to eat beans out of your
pantry for a while or maybe you'll have to go to a food bank or soup
kitchen.  The humiliation you'll feel (or should feel) if that happens will
cause you to do anything to avoid that experience again. Don't ever again
spend more than you make, or you will end up at the food bank.
